===Noun===
{{en-noun|head=[[Aaron]][['s]] [[rod]]|~}}

# Any of [[various]] [[plant]]s with a tall [[flower]]ing [[stem]], especially:
## ''[[Verbascum thapsus]]'', the {{vern|great mullein}}, [[common mullein]], or [[hag-taper]]. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18th century.}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=2}}</ref>
## [[goldenrod|Goldenrod]], the ''[[Solidago]]'' genus of North American plants with yellow flowers.
## ''[[Hylotelephium telephium]]'' (syn. {{taxlink|Sedum telephium|species|ver=200506}}; [[orpine]], [[livelong]], or {{vern|live-forever}}).
# {{lb|en|architecture}} A [[rod]]-shaped [[molding]] decorated with an entwined snake, and sometimes leaves, vines, and/or scrolls.
# {{lb|en|archaic}} A rod with one serpent twined around it, as used by Aaron (differing from the [[caduceus]] of Mercury, which has two serpents).

